        The custom groups are only considered if LayoutStyle is set to LayoutStyle.CUSTOM_GROUPS

        Returns:
        The CustomGroups.
        See Also:

      • getEdgeBundleDescriptors

        public final ItemMapping<IEdge,EdgeBundleDescriptor> getEdgeBundleDescriptors()
        Gets the mapping of edges to their EdgeBundleDescriptor.

        Bundling together multiple edges means that their common parts are to some degree merged into a bundled part. At the source and target point, the edges are again clearly split.

        If an edge is mapped to null, the default descriptor is used.

        Returns:
        The EdgeBundleDescriptors.
        See Also:
        EdgeBundleDescriptor, CircularLayout.getEdgeBundling(), setEdgeBundleDescriptors(ItemMapping)
